#3D TOUCH GUIDE
## Applicability
3D touch can be apply to IOS 9 or later device with 3d touch capabilities like the iPhone 6S/plus, the iPhone 7/Plus, the iPhone 8/Plus or the the iPhoneX.
##Home Screen Quick Actions
The purpose of home screen quick actions is to offer a quick access to parts of your app. You can set a maximum of 4 Quick Actions.
##Adding Short Cut Items
Add static home screen quick actions using the UIApplicationShortcutItems array in the Info.plist file. 

Below are the details of the arry, the dictionary and the string added in the info.plist file.

* UIApplicationShortcutItemType: (requied) a string used to identify the quick action. 
* UIApplicationShortcutItemTitle: (required) a string used to describing the quick action.
* UIApplicationShortcutItemSubtitle: (optional) a text displayed below the title. 
* UIApplicationShortcutItemIconType: (optional) a string that represents your icon in the Assets file.

##Handling 3D Touch Quick Actions
To handle this action, you need to implement the performActionForShortcutItem method in AppDelegate.swift.

```
func application(_ application: UIApplication, performActionFor shortcutItem: UIApplicationShortcutItem, completionHandler: @escaping (Bool) -> Void) {

        completionHandler(handleShortcutItem(withShortcutItem: shortcutItem))
}
```
